*

!steam/
!steam/*
!steam/*/*
!steam/*/*/*
!steam/*/*/*/*
!steam/*/*/*/*/*
!steam/*/*/*/*/*/*
!steam/*/*/*/*/*/*/*

!docs/
!docs/*
!docs/api/
!docs/api/*.rst

!protobufs/
!protobufs/*

!tests/
!tests/*

!vcr/
!vcr/*

!recipes/
!recipes/*
!recipes/*/*
!recipes/*/*/*

# ``.github/`` — issue templates, workflows, FUNDING.
!.github/
!.github/**

# ``scripts/`` — dev-only console scripts (pb-*, vcr-*), registered via
# ``[tool.poetry.scripts]`` in ``pyproject.toml`` and shipped alongside the
# runtime package so ``poetry install`` picks them up.
!scripts/
!scripts/**

# ``typings/`` — local pyright stubs (currently a BuildServices override
# fixing a bug in types-protobuf 7.34).  See ``pyrightconfig.json``.
!typings/
!typings/**

# Poetry manifests + pyright config — the actual project spec, was being
# dropped by the top-level ``*`` rule pre-modernization when the package
# used setup.py + a Makefile.
!pyproject.toml
!poetry.lock
!pyrightconfig.json

# Poetry build output — never committed; the publish workflow regenerates it.
dist/

*.egg-info
*.pyc
.coverage
*.swp
*.bin

# ``.env`` holds a real Steam Web API key (used by ``tests/generete_webauth_vcr.py``
# and the VCR-cassette regeneration flow described in ``.env.example``).  Already
# implicitly denied by the leading ``*`` at the top of this file — explicit rule
# below makes the intent visible, and the ``!.env.example`` line keeps the
# tracked template alongside it so contributors know what shape to fill in.
.env
!.env.example
